            },
            "answer_text": "1 C of unbalanced charge (all positive or all negative) is a really humungous charge in terms of its physical effects because it will suck the charge out of surrounding things to attempt to neutralize itself, so you don't want to be anywhere near it. A typical lightning bolt is only 15 C. However precisely because of that you rarely get unbalanced charge. For example, 1 kg of Iron is about 1000/55.845 = 17.9 moles of iron atoms, or about 17.9*26 moles of electrons plus the same number of positive charges. A mole is 6.02E23 (Avogadro constant) whereas a coulomb is 6.24E18 electrons, so that's 96500 C lurking. ",
